Conclusion:
I select Singles 1969-1981 because its format (a singles/oldies compilation spanning years), likely analog/organic production characteristics, vocal focus and nostalgic sequencing fit my preferences far better than a dance/electronic/house album, which would lean into synthetic production and polished pop/dance aesthetics that I explicitly find off‑putting.

